***************************
* I N S T A L L A T I O N *
***************************
System Requirements
* Operating System: Windows, Linux, OS X
* Core 2 Duo or Athlon X2 at 2.4 GHz or higher
* 4+GB RAM, 2+GB free hard disk space

Software Requirements
* Java 1.7 (or greater) SDK
* Apache ANT

Recommended Development Tools
* GIT Client
* Eclipse Java IDE
 * m2eclipse
 * Groovy-eclipse
 * Freemarker IDE editor (select from JBools tools plugin)

Prerequisits
In order to install SCIPIO, the following prerequisites must be installed properly:
* Java 1.7 (or greater) SDK
 * Download and Install
 * Set JAVA_HOME Path
 * Validate Settings

Installation
In order to install, the following steps must be taken:

1. Open your command line, go to the extracted folder and run:
a. Linux ./install.sh
b. OS X: ./install.sh
c. Windows: install.bat

2. From the same command line run:
a. Linux ./tools/start.sh
b. OS X: bash /tools/start.sh
c. Windows: /tools/start.bat

3. To access the application visit the OFBiz Dashboard:
OFBiz Dashboard: http://localhost:8080/webtools

4. To access the OFBiz Applications from the Dashboard use:
Username: admin
Password: scipio


                            Congratulations, you have installed SCIPIO!


Optional Configuration
* OFBiz-related Configuration
  https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/OFBTECH/Apache+OFBiz+Technical+Production+Setup+Guide
* Memory allocation
  https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/OFBTECH/Apache+OFBiz+Technical+Production+Setup+Guide#ApacheOFBizTechnicalProductionSetupGuide-MemorySettings

